        <body>
            <p>EngJu(f)</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                <date>13. Dec. 1830</date>.</p>
            <p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am now closing the castor oil business for this<lb/> year. and am
                desirous of settling all accts connected with it.<lb/> You must do me the favor to
                call upon <sic>Doctr</sic> Dyott. and request him<lb/> to pay you the bill of $1614
                farther orders for bottles will come<lb/> into next year's business.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Request <persName>Mr. Sol: Levy</persName> to close the oil in his
                hands at one<lb/> dollar if he cannot do better-<lb/> Yr.</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">D. Judah</persName>
            </p>
            <p>EngRe(b)</p>
            <p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I received your letter per <persName>Mr. A. Phillips</persName> I
                was not at<lb/> home when he <sic>Brought</sic> yours He did not leave word where he
                stayed<lb/> Else I should have been glad to call on him and invite him to my<lb/>
                house. <persName>Mr. Jacobs</persName> the (Hazan (Shochet)? is gone to
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>. He is not<lb/> much to depend on what he
                says He told us he received $200 Doll-<lb/>ars of <persName>Mr. Etting</persName>
                but <persName>Mr. Etting</persName> told us last <date>Shabot</date> he only<lb/>
                paid him for himself and son and that figures 60 dollars so you<lb/> must not
                believe what he says. We received a letter from <add>?</add><lb/> she is well
                    <add>?</add> Give my respect to <persName>Mr &amp; Mrs Peixotto</persName> and
                the young<lb/>
                <sic>laydes</sic> and the young gentleman and the <sic>samefrom</sic> your Aunt.
                No<lb/> news I remain your friend</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Zalma Rehine</persName>
            </p>
            <p>I have not seen <persName>Mr. Cohen</persName> yet so let that stand as it is at
                pre-<lb/>sent. I'm glad that your book is liked in
                <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>.</p>
            <p>Letter addressed to <sic><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leezer</addressee></sic><lb/> Solo:
                    <persName>Henry</persName>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
        </body>
